{"in": {"title": "Questing Lores", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">The story of the confused Comp sci student</span>", "lines": ["NARRATOR: Once upon a time in&nbsp; a place not so far away there lived a student named Ali. Ali had enrolled in a computer science class for summer but for the first week of the class he was travelling with little access to internet. He came back home diving into his work trying to figure out what is what.&nbsp;", "ALI: Computer science. This should be easy after all I do know python already.&nbsp;", "SCENE: https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/eer-ie-music-8s.mp3 (no wait)&nbsp;", "ALI: Wait a second what is this.&nbsp;", "NARRATOR: After thoroughly reading through the syllabus and course Ali had discovered quests.&nbsp;", "Ali: I don't understand how do I complete a quest Ali: How do I even open it Ali: When is the due date Ali: What is the task Ali: where is the coding Ali: (whisper) I'm so lost... Narrator: 1 hour later... after some digging Ali was able to find the answers to these questions. Ali: (x-loud) I get it. Ali: we are supposed to play around with the interface and familiarize ourselves and send our experiments to Prof Anand. Ali: (soft) I hope I understood it correctly. I still don't quite understand how to go to the next quest. In the subreddit I also see a lot of people mention the coding problems they are interacting with when I still haven't seen them. Ali: Either way this is a step forward and every quest starts with the first step. Narrator: That is how our young confused student began his quest of understanding C++. He has yet to figure out whether he is headed in the right direction but at the very least he has started to explore his surroundings. The next step is to figure out if he is going the right way. Note to professor: Hi Prof Anand. I wasn't sure if this was the assignment for the first quest. I just got back from a family trip yesterday (June 3rd) in which I had very limited access to wifi and was unable to properly delve into the contents of the course until today. I assumed that you wanted us to do something like this based off the create your own script quest lore and I hope I didn't misunderstand the task and if I did I apoligize and I'll figure it out as soon as possible. best Ali :)"], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Matthew", "Ali": "Joanna", "Persona1": "Joanna", "I'm so confused (no wait)": "Joanna", "I'm so confused&nbsp;": "Joanna", "Scene": "Joanna", "Narrator": "Joanna", "Note to professor": "Joanna", "ALI": "Joanna", "SCENE": "Joanna"}}, "out": {"cache_id": "c19000a1ad30e718350e898ee7fa4fbd", "audio_objects": [["91cc45ab91cc8867e10b2ef1465305ea-once-upon-a-time-in--a-pl---", 0], ["bf4935ac5c95d8bf7046dbee368591c2-computer-science--this-sh---", 0], ["https://lores.nonlinearmedia.org/res/mp3/misc/eer-ie-music-8s.mp3", 1], ["6251a01b97695af7a7344304d90aca3a-wait-a-second-what-is-thi---", 0], ["c3f16388bc42848d8ff65ea70d09a165-after-thoroughly-reading----", 0], ["d9f10aaba5f6776b8c606fff8e144a1b-ali--i-don-t-understand-h---", 0]]}}